---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import PolicyArticle from "../components/layout/PolicyArticle.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../config/site";
---

<MainLayout title="Privacy Policy">
  <PolicyArticle title="Crystord: Privacy Policy" updatedAt="June 8, 2026">

    <section>
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>Aleutheris operates two Crystord products: the Crystord Google Workspace Add-on (the
      "Add-on"), which synchronises data between Google Sheets™ and Google Slides™, and the Crystord
      web application at <a href="https://app.crystord.com">app.crystord.com</a> (the "App"), which
      provides account management and access control for the Crystord platform. This privacy policy
      explains how information is collected, used, and protected across both products.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Products Covered by This Policy</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Workspace Add-on:</strong> Installed from the Google Workspace Marketplace
        and runs within Google Slides™. Accesses Google Sheets™ and Slides™ data in your Google
        account to perform synchronisation.</li>
        <li><strong>Crystord Web Application (app.crystord.com):</strong> A web-based platform for
        signing in to your Crystord account. Collects account credentials to authenticate users.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Collection and Access</h2>

      <h3>Google Workspace Add-on</h3>
      <p>When you use the Add-on, it accesses the following Google user data:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Sheets™ content:</strong> Read access to the specific spreadsheets you
        select as data sources for synchronisation.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Slides™ content:</strong> Read and write access to the specific
        presentations you are editing, to identify and replace placeholder variables.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>These permissions are limited to the files you explicitly connect and are required solely
      to perform the synchronisation function.</p>

      <h3>Crystord Web Application</h3>
      <p>When you sign in to the Crystord App, the following information is processed:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email address and password:</strong> Submitted at sign-in to authenticate your
        account. Passwords are never stored in plain text.</li>
        <li><strong>Session token:</strong> Issued after successful authentication to maintain your
        signed-in session. Stored only in your browser for the duration of your session.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The App does not collect browsing behaviour, location data, or device identifiers beyond
      what is necessary for authentication.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Usage</h2>
      <p>Crystord's use of data adheres to the following principles:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Add-on data:</strong> Google Sheets™ and Slides™ content is accessed solely to
        perform the synchronisation you request. It is not retained, analysed for commercial
        purposes, or shared with third parties.</li>
        <li><strong>App account data:</strong> Your email address is used to identify your account.
        It is not used for marketing without your explicit consent.</li>
        <li><strong>No profiling:</strong> We do not build profiles of user behaviour or preferences
        from either product.</li>
        <li><strong>No AI training:</strong> Your data is not used to train machine learning or
        artificial intelligence models.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Crystord's use of information received from Google APIs adheres to the
      <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>,
      including the Limited Use Requirements.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>We do not sell, trade, or transfer your personal data to third parties. Data is shared only
      in the following limited circumstances:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google APIs:</strong> Add-on operations call Google Sheets™ and Slides™ APIs as
        required by the synchronisation function. No other external services receive your document
        data.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> We may disclose information if required by law or to
        protect the rights and safety of users.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Storage and Protection</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Add-on — no external storage:</strong> Google Sheets™ and Slides™ content is
        never stored on Aleutheris servers. All document data resides within your Google account and
        Drive.</li>
        <li><strong>App — account data:</strong> Account credentials are stored securely on
        Crystord platform infrastructure. Passwords are stored using a one-way cryptographic hash.
        Session tokens are short-lived and invalidated on sign-out.</li>
        <li><strong>Transport security:</strong> All communication between your browser, the App,
        and Google services uses HTTPS encryption.</li>
        <li><strong>Apps Script infrastructure:</strong> The Add-on runs within Google Apps Script,
        which benefits from Google's security and compliance infrastructure.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Exception Logging</h2>
      <p>Both the Add-on and the App use technical logging for error detection and reliability
      improvements. Logs record error types, timestamps, and operational context. They do not
      include the content of your Google documents or your account password. Exception logs are
      retained for up to 30 days and then automatically deleted.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>User Controls</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Add-on permissions:</strong> You can revoke the Add-on's access to your Google
        account at any time via
        <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">myaccount.google.com/permissions</a>.
        Revoking access immediately stops all document data access.</li>
        <li><strong>Add-on uninstall:</strong> Uninstalling the Add-on removes all associated
        Google account permissions.</li>
        <li><strong>App account:</strong> You may contact us to request deletion of your Crystord
        account and associated data at any time.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
      <h3>Add-on</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>No Google document content is retained after a synchronisation session completes. All
        processing occurs transiently within Google's infrastructure.</li>
        <li>Configuration data (such as selected Sheet IDs) is stored in your Slides™ file
        properties within your Google account, not on external servers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Web Application</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Account data is retained for as long as your account remains active.</li>
        <li>You may request deletion of your account and all associated data by contacting us at
        <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a>. Requests are
        processed within 30 days.</li>
        <li>Exception logs are deleted after 30 days.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Compliance</h2>
      <p>Crystord's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs adheres to the Google
      API Services User Data Policy, including the Limited Use Requirements. Data is used only to
      provide the features you request and is never used for advertising, profiling, or purposes
      not disclosed in this policy.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>This policy may be updated when product features change or legal requirements evolve.
      Material changes will be announced on this page with an updated revision date. Continued use
      of either product after a policy update constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>For questions or requests regarding this privacy policy or your personal data, contact
      Aleutheris at
      <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <small slot="trademark">Google Sheets™ and Google Slides™ are trademarks of Google LLC.</small>
  </PolicyArticle>
</MainLayout>
